        "524": {
          "vnum": 524,
          "name": "Lowode Hills",
          "description": "Shedevat's trail through the Lowode expertly weaves through the thickly overgrown hills, and comes to a rough end before a large clearing of loosely packed, mineral-rich soil. The path continues further south, and retreats back into the forest to the northeast. A narrow seam of copper glints from the rock face.",
